  <title translate="true">ALLOTMENTS: Farm Process V4 Allotment Options</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">ALLOTMENTS: Farm Process V4 Allotment Options</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The ALLOTMENTS: Farm Process V4 Allotment Options pane is used to activate the allotment options in the Farm Process in MODFLOW-OWHM version 2 and specify surface water or groundwater allotments for it. It is in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Farm-Process-(for-MODFLOW-OWHM" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Farm Process</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> group on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MODFLOW_Packages_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Packages and Programs</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Farm_Allotment_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Farm Allotment</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box is only used with MODFLOW-OWHM version 1. It is not used with MODFLOW-OWHM version 2.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Both </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Surface Water Allotment</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Groundwater Allotment</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> can be static or transient. Both are specified in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Farms_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Water Balance Subregions</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box. There are three options for how the allotments are specified.</text></para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">RATE</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> (L</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super;" translate="true">3</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">/T) volumetric rate limit.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">VOLUME</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> (L</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super;" translate="true">3</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">) per stress period.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">HEIGHT</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> (L) per stress period - multiplied by water balance subregion irrigated area to get volume per stress period.</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Use of </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">VOLUME</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">HEIGHT</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> will cause incorrect model input if ModelMuse inserts additional stress periods because some boundary conditions are defined at times that do not correspond to the times defined in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MODFLOW_Time_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">MODFLOW Time</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box..</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Strong"></para>
  </body>
